resources.name: Detailed information on public opinion website

description:
This report addresses the participation of European Union citizens in cultural activities. It is divided into chapters covering:
Television, the programmes that citizens watch and their favourite television programmes
The frequency with which Europeans listen to radio and their favourite radio programmes
The use of computers and the Internet in the European Union
Reading habits, be it books, newspapers or magazines
The music that Europeans listen to, and the concerts they have attended
The practice of artistic activities


#####The results by volumes are distributed as follows:
* Volume A: Countries
* Volume AA: Groups of countries
* Volume A' (AP): Trends
* Volume AA' (AAP): Trends of groups of countries
* Volume B: EU/socio-demographics
* Volume C: Country/socio-demographics
title: Special Eurobarometer 158: Europeans' participation in cultural activities
name: S213_56_0_EBS158
